outline:
1. to be left over, remain, remain over, leave
    1. (Qal) remainder (participle)
    2. (Niphal) to be left over, remain over, be left behind
    3. (Hiphil)
      1. to leave over, leave
      2. to save over, preserve alive
      3. to excel, show pre-eminence
      4. to show excess, have more than enough, have an excess
kjv_def: excel, leave (a remnant), left behind, too much, make plenteous, preserve, (be, let) remain(-der, -ing, -nant), reserve, residue, rest.
strongs_def: to jut over or exceed; by implication, to excel; (intransitively) to remain or be left; causatively, to leave, cause to abound, preserve
